# design-token-lint

> **Emitted only when `{{TOKENS_FILE}}` is set.** A project with no design-token file does not get this gate — and nothing in the harness may reference it.

The design system's core rule: components reference **semantic tokens only**, never primitives or raw values. This skill catches violations mechanically.

## What to flag

- **Raw hex / rgb / hsl** color literals in components (`#`, `rgb(`, `hsl(`) — must be a semantic token from `{{TOKENS_FILE}}`. Exception: inside `{{TOKENS_FILE}}` itself.
- **Raw color for status/identity** — status must come from the semantic status tokens, never a bespoke color; identity/avatar colors from the identity scale, never an ad-hoc hue.
- **Ad-hoc spacing / radius / type** — magic px for margin/padding/gap/border-radius/font-size that doesn't map to a spacing/radius/type token. Allow `0`, 1px hairlines, and `100%` / `auto`.
- **Hard-coded motion** — durations/eases not from the motion tokens; and any motion that ignores `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- **Non-token font families / weights** outside the font tokens.
- **Primitive-token use in components** — components should use *semantic* tokens; flag direct use of a raw primitive where a semantic token exists.
- **Dark mode** — any component that hard-codes a light-only color instead of relying on the semantic token that re-declares under the dark theme selector.

## How

Grep/AST the frontend sources for the patterns above; allowlist `{{TOKENS_FILE}}`. Prefer wiring this as a stylelint rule + an ESLint rule so it runs in CI and fails PRs rather than depending on an agent remembering to run it.

## Output

A list of violations (`file:line`, the offending value, the token that should replace it). Zero violations = pass. For CI, exit non-zero on any violation.

When dispatched by the orchestrator at a join, this is **report-only** — a reviewer never edits the code it judges. A unit agent running it mid-unit may fix its own violations.
